# 📘 AWS CloudWatch – Scenario-Based Debugging Guide

---

# 🧠 What is CloudWatch used for?

* Monitoring (metrics)
* Logging (application/system logs)
* Alerting (alarms)

---

# 🚀 Core Concepts

---

## 📊 Metrics vs Logs

| Type    | Example               |
| ------- | --------------------- |
| Metrics | CPU, latency, network |
| Logs    | Errors, stack traces  |

---

## ⚠️ Default vs Custom Metrics

* ✅ Default: CPU, Network
* ❌ Not default: Memory (needs agent)

---

## 🔔 Alarms

* Threshold-based alerts
* Evaluation period matters
* Can trigger actions (SNS, Auto Scaling)

---

# 🧩 Scenario-Based Questions

---

## 1️⃣ High CPU but no alert

### ❓ Problem:

CPU = 90%, but no alert triggered

### 🔍 Causes:

* Threshold too high
* Wrong metric selected
* Evaluation period too long

### ✅ Fix:

* Adjust threshold
* Reduce evaluation window

---

## 2️⃣ Application slow but CPU normal

### ❓ Problem:

System slow, but CPU/memory fine

### 🔍 Causes:

* Disk I/O bottleneck
* Network latency
* DB slowness

### ✅ Fix:

* Check disk metrics
* Check DB performance

---

## 3️⃣ Logs not appearing

### ❓ Problem:

Application logs missing

### 🔍 Causes:

* CloudWatch agent not installed
* IAM role missing permission
* Log group misconfigured

### ✅ Fix:

* Install/configure agent
* Fix IAM role

---

## 4️⃣ Too many alerts (alert fatigue)

### ❓ Problem:

Too many alerts, mostly useless

### 🔍 Causes:

* Threshold too sensitive
* No filtering
* No aggregation

### ✅ Fix:

* Tune thresholds
* Use composite alarms

---

## 5️⃣ Instance not responding

### ❓ Problem:

EC2 becomes unresponsive

### 🔍 Causes:

* CPU spike
* Instance status check failed
* Memory exhaustion

### ✅ Fix:

* Check status checks
* Monitor memory (custom metric)

---

## 6️⃣ Auto Scaling not triggering

### ❓ Problem:

Traffic increases, but no scaling

### 🔍 Causes:

* Alarm not linked to ASG
* Wrong metric used
* Cooldown period

### ✅ Fix:

* Verify alarm-action mapping
* Adjust cooldown

---

## 7️⃣ 5xx errors increasing

### ❓ Problem:

Error rate increasing

### 🔍 Causes:

* Backend failure
* Target unhealthy
* App crash

### ✅ Fix:

* Check LB metrics
* Check application logs

---

## 8️⃣ Memory issue not visible

### ❓ Problem:

App crashes due to memory, but no metric

### 🔍 Cause:

* Memory not collected by default

### ✅ Fix:

* Install CloudWatch agent

---

## 9️⃣ High network latency

### ❓ Problem:

Slow requests

### 🔍 Causes:

* Cross-AZ traffic
* Network congestion
* High load

### ✅ Fix:

* Check network metrics
* Optimize placement

---

## 🔟 Need proactive alerting

### ❓ Problem:

Want alert before failure

### 🔍 Solution:

* Use anomaly detection
* Use trend-based alarms

---

# 🧠 Debug Flow (INTERVIEW GOLD)

```text id="u6d4os"
1. Check metrics (CPU, latency, network)
2. Check logs (errors, exceptions)
3. Correlate metrics + logs
4. Identify root cause
```

---

# 🚨 Common Mistakes

* ❌ Assuming CPU tells everything
* ❌ Ignoring logs
* ❌ Not configuring alarms properly
* ❌ Missing custom metrics (memory)

---

# 🎯 Interview One-Liners

* “CloudWatch provides metrics, logs, and alarms”
* “Memory is not a default metric”
* “I correlate metrics with logs to debug issues”
* “Alarm behavior depends on threshold and evaluation period”

---

# 💪 Final Takeaway

```text id="2nljsl"
